<subSubSection id="C336F9CAFF824E4F65D1FAE9FC8165CF" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B93AA41FF824E4F65D1FAE9FC8165CF" blockId="3.[136,1452,1272,2091]" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">
Diagnosis:—Pileus 
<quantity id="4CD407A4FF824E4F64F1FAE9FDB7653E" box="[413,519,1308,1335]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8–15 mm</quantity>
diam, conical to paraboloid, yellowish ochraceous to pale brownish. Stipe 42–72 × 
<quantity id="4CD407A4FF824E4F65E4FAB5FF576552" box="[136,231,1344,1371]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 mm</quantity>
, cylindrical. Lamellae light ochraceous to light brown. Basidiospores 9.9–12.2 × 5.6–7.0 μm, amygdaliform, ellipsoid to elongated-ellipsoid, verrucose, light ocher-brown. Cheilocystidia 41–69 × 7–10 μm, lageniform to subfusiform, hyaline to yellowish. Basidia narrowly clavate, 24–35 × 8–11 μm, with 
<specimenCount id="9D2A61C8FF824E4F612FFA7DFB0D65AA" box="[1091,1213,1416,1443]" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="generic" typeStatus="types">three types</specimenCount>
of sterigmata: thornshaped, long pine needle-like, and 2-branched antler-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C336F9CAFF824E4F65D1FA25FCBB65E3" box="[189,779,1488,1515]" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
