<subSubSection id="C336F9CAFF824E4865D1F995FC536141" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B93AA41FF824E4F65D1F995FEBA6727" blockId="3.[136,1452,1272,2091]" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">
Description:— 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF824E4F6408F995FE1A6673" box="[356,426,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Pileus</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CD407A4FF824E4F64D8F995FD936672" box="[436,547,1632,1659]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8–15 mm</quantity>
diam, conical to paraboloid or approximately campanulate when young, then gradually convex, some umbonate, surface smooth, dry, initially golden brown (5D7), oak brown (5D6) to raw Sienna (6D7) when mature, salmon (6A4) to flesh color (6B3) at the center, hygrophanous at the margin. Context thin, flesh color (6B3). 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF824E4F6474F939FE3066EF" box="[280,384,1740,1766]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Lamellae</emphasis>
adnate, moderately sparse, flesh color (6B3), light brown (6D8) to brown (6C6). 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF824E4F607CF939FAF866EF" box="[1296,1352,1740,1766]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Stipe</emphasis>
42–72 × 
<quantity id="4CD407A4FF824E4F65E4F905FF576702" box="[136,231,1776,1803]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 mm</quantity>
, cylindrical, hollow, fragile, light brown to brown (6C6), dry, inconspicuously pruinose over the entire length (
<figureCitation id="1317B6C4FF824E4F65FCF8E1FF4D6727" box="[144,253,1812,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–3" captionStartId="4.[136,243,1939,1961]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,302,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-103@4.[196,1391,314,1113]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–3. Galerina variibasidia (2: HMJAU58768 holotype!, 3: HMJAU58769 paratype!) Basidiomes among mossy layer on rotting coniferous stumps. Bars: A, B=1 cm. Photos by Xiaoliang Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5606522/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B93AA41FF824E4865D1F8CDFC536141" blockId="3.[136,1452,1272,2091]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1452,158,329]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B9587653FF824E4F65D1F8CDFEEB675B" box="[189,347,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Basidiospores</emphasis>
9.9–12.2 × 5.6–7 μm, 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF824E4F6703F8CDFD33675B" box="[623,643,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">
<collectionCode id="ED3D3284FF824E4F6703F8CDFD33675B" box="[623,643,1848,1874]" country="Ecuador" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14273" name="Universidad Central" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="Herbarium">Q</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
= 1.5–2.1, amygdaliform, ellipsoid to elongate–ellipsoid or narrowly ellipsoid to fusiform, brownish orange (6 
<specimenCode id="DB8A023AFF824E4F670DF8A9FD32677E" box="[609,642,1884,1911]" collectionCode="C" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="Herbarium">C8</specimenCode>
) to light brown (6D8) in 5% KOH solution, verrucose, ornamentation consisting of low, broad, irregular warts, plage distinctive, dextrinoid (
<figureCitation id="1317B6C4FF824E4F66D3F875FB976793" box="[959,1063,1920,1946]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1974,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,199,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[151,1436,190,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Galerina variibasidia (HMJAU58768, holotype!) A−B. Cheilocystidia C. Pleurocystidia D. Basidiospores E. Basidia Bars: A–E=10μm. Photos by Xiaoliang Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5608399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5608399/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Figs. 4D</figureCitation>
, 5 
<collectionCode id="ED3D3284FF824E4F6129F875FBEA6792" box="[1093,1114,1920,1947]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
). 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF824E4F611EF875FB786793" box="[1138,1224,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Basidia</emphasis>
24–35 × 8–11 μm, narrowly clavate, sterigmata variable, usually three forms: thorn-shaped, abundant, 2 or 4, 3–6 μm long (
<figureCitation id="1317B6C4FF824E4F607BF851FAD467B6" box="[1303,1380,1956,1983]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1974,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,199,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[151,1436,190,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Galerina variibasidia (HMJAU58768, holotype!) A−B. Cheilocystidia C. Pleurocystidia D. Basidiospores E. Basidia Bars: A–E=10μm. Photos by Xiaoliang Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5608399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5608399/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
Ef–g); long pine needle-like, 2 or 4, 10–27 μm long (
<figureCitation id="1317B6C4FF824E4F67F2F83DFD5D67EA" box="[670,749,1992,2019]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1974,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,199,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[151,1436,190,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Galerina variibasidia (HMJAU58768, holotype!) A−B. Cheilocystidia C. Pleurocystidia D. Basidiospores E. Basidia Bars: A–E=10μm. Photos by Xiaoliang Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5608399" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5608399/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
Ea–d); and 2-branched antler-shaped including 
<specimenCount id="9D2A61C8FF824E4F6067F83CFACC67EA" box="[1291,1404,1993,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="30" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
, the first 
<typeStatus id="549714E3FF824E4F65D2F818FF5E680E" box="[190,238,2029,2055]" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
with one bifurcate sterigma (
<figureCitation id="1317B6C4FF824E4F672DF819FD2D680E" box="[577,669,2028,2055]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,203,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-27@6.[179,1408,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Galerina variibasidia (HMJAU58768, holotype!) A. Basidiomata B. Basidiospores C. Pileipellis D. Basidia E. Pleurocystidia F. Stipitipellis G. Cheilocystidia Bars: A=1 cm, B=5 μm, C–G=10 μm. Drawings by Xiaoliang Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5606524/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
), another 
<typeStatus id="549714E3FF824E4F667CF818FCF0680E" box="[784,832,2029,2055]" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
with two branched sterigmata (
<figureCitation id="1317B6C4FF824E4F61C0F819FAB8680E" box="[1196,1288,2028,2055]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,203,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-27@6.[179,1408,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Galerina variibasidia (HMJAU58768, holotype!) A. Basidiomata B. Basidiospores C. Pileipellis D. Basidia E. Pleurocystidia F. Stipitipellis G. Cheilocystidia Bars: A=1 cm, B=5 μm, C–G=10 μm. Drawings by Xiaoliang Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5606524/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
), both forking into antlers. 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF824E4F6470F7E5FE0E6823" box="[284,446,2064,2090]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="30">Cheilocystidia</emphasis>
numerous, 41–69 × 7–10 μm, thin-walled, densely packed at the edge, lageniform to subfusiform, ventricose near the base and gradually tapering towards the apex, tip blunt and rounded, mostly hyaline, occasionally light yellowish or near Pompeian yellow (5 
<specimenCode id="DB8A023AFF854E486669FF37FC9860D4" box="[773,808,194,221]" collectionCode="C" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" type="Herbarium">C6</specimenCode>
) in 5% KOH solution. 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF854E48615DFF37FB6360D5" box="[1073,1235,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pleurocystidia</emphasis>
scattered, 45–62 × 8–11 μm, like the cheilocystidia. 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF854E486496FF13FDDC6109" box="[506,620,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pileipellis</emphasis>
a cutis of interwoven hyphae, with cylindrical to inflated segments, 13–21 μm broad, thin-walled, hyaline, pileocystidia absent. 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF854E4867B4FEFFFCE8612D" box="[728,856,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Stipitipellis</emphasis>
a cutis of interwoven hyphae. 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF854E4861C1FEFFFAF9612D" box="[1197,1353,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Caulocystidia</emphasis>
44–68 × 9–12 μm, like the cheilocystidia. 
<emphasis id="B9587653FF854E486492FEDBFD656141" box="[510,725,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Clamp connections</emphasis>
numerous in all tissues.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
